comment:
***************************************************************************
     * A ModuleProperties describes a given sound trigger hardware module
     * managed by the native sound trigger service. Each module has a unique
     * ID used to target any API call to this paricular module. Module
     * properties are returned by listModules() method.
     *
     ***************************************************************************

variables.name: AUDIO_CAPABILITY_ECHO_CANCELLATION
variables.comment:
* If set the underlying module supports AEC.
         * Describes bit field {@link ModuleProperties#mAudioCapabilities}

variables.name: AUDIO_CAPABILITY_NOISE_SUPPRESSION
variables.comment:
* If set, the underlying module supports noise suppression.
         * Describes bit field {@link ModuleProperties#mAudioCapabilities}

methods.name: public int getId()
methods.comment: Unique module ID provided by the native service

methods.name: public String getImplementor()
methods.comment: human readable voice detection engine implementor

methods.name: public String getDescription()
methods.comment: human readable voice detection engine description

methods.name: public UUID getUuid()
methods.comment: Unique voice engine Id (changes with each version)

methods.name: public String getSupportedModelArch()
methods.comment:
* String naming the architecture used for running the supported models.
         * (eg. a platform running models on a DSP could implement this string to convey the DSP
         * architecture used)

methods.name: public int getMaxSoundModels()
methods.comment: Maximum number of active sound models

methods.name: public int getMaxUsers()
methods.comment: Maximum number of users per key phrase

methods.name: public boolean isCaptureTransitionSupported()
methods.comment: Supports seamless transition to capture mode after recognition

methods.name: public int getMaxBufferMillis()
methods.comment: Maximum buffering capacity in ms if supportsCaptureTransition() is true

methods.name: public boolean isConcurrentCaptureSupported()
methods.comment: Supports capture by other use cases while detection is active

methods.name: public int getPowerConsumptionMw()
methods.comment: Rated power consumption when detection is active with TDB silence/sound/speech ratio

methods.name: public boolean isTriggerReturnedInEvent()
methods.comment:
Returns the trigger (key phrase) capture in the binary data of the
         * recognition callback event

methods.name: public int getAudioCapabilities()
methods.comment:
* Bit field encoding of the AudioCapabilities
         * supported by the firmware.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@SuppressLint("MissingNullability") Parcel dest, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@SuppressLint("MissingNullability") Parcel dest, int flags)
